age-services/iiif/service:ndnp:gu:batch_gu_grouch_ver01:data:2022239691:00517010340:1923091701:0302/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/2022239691/1923-09-17/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "rights": ["<p>The Library of Congress believes that the newspapers in Chronicling America are in the public domain or have no known copyright restrictions.  Newspapers published in the United States more than 95 years ago are in the public domain in their entirety. Any newspapers in Chronicling America that were published less than 95 years ago are also believed to be in the public domain, but may contain some copyrighted third party materials. Researchers using newspapers published less than 95 years ago should be alert for modern content (for example, registered and renewed for copyright and published with notice) that may be copyrighted.  Responsibility for making an independent legal assessment of an item and securing any necessary permissions ultimately rests with persons desiring to use the item.</p>\n<p>The NEH awardee responsible for producing each digital object is presented in the Chronicling America page display, below the page image  \u2013 e.g. Image produced by the Library of Congress. For more information on current NDNP awardees, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html\">https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html</a>.</p>\n<p>For more information on Library of Congress policies and disclaimers regarding rights and reproductions, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html\">https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html</a></p>"], "score": 14.017402, "shard": "02", "shelf_id": "2022239691, 1923-09-17, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "source_group": "ndnp/gu", "source_modified": "2000-01-01T12:00:00Z", "subject": ["cordele (ga.)", "newspapers", "crisp", "crisp county (ga.)", "cordele", "georgia", "crisp county", "united states"], "subject_headings": ["Cordele (Ga.)--Newspapers", "Crisp County (Ga.)--Newspapers", "Georgia--Cordele", "Georgia--Crisp County", "United States--Georgia--Crisp--Cordele"], "subjects": [{"cordele": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:cordele&fo=json"}, {"cordele (ga.)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:cordele+%28ga.%29&fo=json"}, {"crisp": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:crisp&fo=json"}, {"crisp county": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:crisp+county&fo=json"}, {"crisp county (ga.)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:crisp+county+%28ga.%29&fo=json"}, {"georgia": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:georgia&fo=json"}, {"newspapers": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:newspapers&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:united+states&fo=json"}], "timestamp": "2024-05-22T23:43:30.545Z", "title": "The Cordele dispatch and daily sentinel (Cordele, Georgia), September 17, 1923", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2022239691/1923-09-17/ed-1/"}, "locations": null, "method": "mets_filesec", "more_like_this": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2022239691/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2022239691", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/4673761a-9b95-56a4-90bb-254d8c0fd57f"], "batch": ["gu_fozzie_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1920", "description": ["Daily (except Saturday) Began in May or June 1920; ceased with: Volume 9, number 122 (April 7, 1926). Some issues have named section: Le petite dispatch, written by local high school students, <April 1926> Appears to be merger of: Cordele dispatch and: Cordele daily sentinel. Vol. 3, no. 171 (June 2, 1920) (microfilm surrogate); title from masthead. Volume 9, number 122 (April 7, 1926) (microfilm surrogate). Cordele dispatch (Cordele, Ga. : 1926) (DLC) 2022239700 (OCoLC)1330250546"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:11.942Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-04", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-04"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2022239691/", "image_url": [], "index": 4, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [31.9691202, -83.7826846], "location": ["crisp", "crisp county", "georgia", "cordele", "united states"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-83.7826846, 31.9691202], "number": ["sn89053138", "online resource", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2022239691/1920-06-02/ed-1/", "2024-05-12t17:32:27.269094", "2025-09-17t10:50:15.800000", "1668", "2022239699", "2995-956x", "2022239691", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2022239691/1926-04-07/ed-1/", "original", "univ of georgia", "1316790520", "2022239700"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["the cordele dispatch and daily sentinel (cordele, georgia) 1920-1926", "catalog", "chronicling america", "serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 88.22539, "shelf_id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/2022239691", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "usnd", "catalog"], "subject": ["cordele (ga.)", "newspapers", "crisp", "crisp county (ga.)", "cordele", "georgia", "crisp county", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-07-22T07:26:06.767Z", "title": "The Cordele dispatch and daily sentinel", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2022239691/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2024271005/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "19??", "dates": ["[1900 TO 1920]"], "description": ["Daily (except Sat.), Nov. 15, 1917-1920 Print ceased in May or June 1920. \"Official organ of the city of Cordele and Crisp County.\"--volume VII, no. 40 (January 5, 1916), page [4]. \"Official organ of Crisp County.\"--vol. VIII, no. 5 (May 3, 1916). Has separately titled section, <May 30, 1917->: High school news. Stated frequency and actual frequency may differ. May be some irregularities in enumeration and chronology. May contain special issue called: D.A.R. Edition. This seems more likely to have been a one-time special issue than a true separate edition. Semiweekly edition carrying its own enumeration may have been included as part of this title during some periods when title was published daily from Nov. 15, 1917- . Despite presence of frequency edition statements, cannot be determined whether the semiweekly edition constituted an entirely separate publication. There may have been days when the semiweekly edition was the only paper printed for the day and intended to function also as the daily issue. Some issues with semiweekly edition statement give frequency as daily in publisher's block. Appears to have merged with: Cordele daily sentinel to form: Cordele dispatch and daily sentinel. Volume VII, No. 40 (January 5, 1916); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed January 10, 2024). Vol. 3, No. 165 (May 26, 1920) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed January 10, 2024). Cordele daily sentinel 2995-9500 (DLC) 2024271006 (OCoLC)1365768741 Cordele dispatch and daily sentinel 2995-9578 (DLC) 2024271007 (OCoLC)1365639853"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:38:08.561Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2024271005/", "image_url": [], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "location": ["crisp", "crisp county", "georgia", "cordele", "united states"], "number": ["2026-04-13t21:30:13", "online resource", "2024271006", "2024271005", "1365769087", "2024271007", "2995-9454"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "the cordele dispatch (cordele georgia;cordele, georgia) 19??-1920 [online resource]"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 79.01716, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["cordele (ga.)", "journaux", "newspapers", "crisp", "crisp county (ga.)", "cordele", "georgia", "crisp county", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:13:21.366Z", "title": "The Cordele dispatch", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2024271005/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2024271006/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1919", "dates": ["[1919 TO 1920]"], "description": ["Daily (except Sunday) Print began September 1, 1919; ceased May or June 1920. \"Official Organ County of Crisp and City of Cordele.\"--page [4], Volume 1, number 121 (May 20, 1920). Appears to have merged with: Cordele dispatch (Cordele, Ga. : 1916) to form: Cordele dispatch and daily sentinel. Volume 1, Number 121 (May 20, 1920); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed January 10, 2024). Volume 1, Number 227 (May 27, 1920) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed January 10, 2024). Cordele dispatch 2995-9454 (DLC) 2024271005 (OCoLC)1365769087 Cordele dispatch and daily sentinel 2995-9578 (DLC) 2024271007 (OCoLC)1365639853"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:38:08.561Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2024271006/", "image_url": [], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["crisp", "crisp county", "georgia", "cordele", "united states"], "number": ["online resource", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "2024271006", "2995-9500", "2024271005", "2024271007", "1365768741"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["cordele daily sentinel (cordele, ga.) 1919-1920 [online resource]", "serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 79.01716, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["cordele (ga.)", "journaux", "newspapers", "crisp", "crisp county (ga.)", "cordele", "georgia", "crisp county", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:13:21.366Z", "title": "Cordele daily sentinel", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2024271006/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2024271007/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1920", "dates": ["[1920 TO 1926]"], "description": ["Daily (except Saturday) Print began in May or June 1920; ceased with volume 9, number 122 (April 7, 1926). Some issues have named section: Le petite dispatch, written by local high school students, <April 1926> Appears to be merger of: Cordele dispatch and: Cordele daily sentinel. Vol. 3, No. 171 (June 2, 1920); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed January 10, 2024). Volume No. 9, Number 122 (April 7, 1926) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed January 10, 2024). Cordele dispatch (Cordele, Ga. : 1926) 2995-9616 (DLC) 2024271008 (OCoLC)1371042241"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:38:08.561Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2024271007/", "image_url": [], "index": 7, "language": ["english"], "location": ["crisp", "crisp county", "georgia", "cordele", "united states"], "number": ["2026-04-13t21:30:13", "online resource", "2995-9578", "2024271006", "2024271005", "1365639853", "2024271008", "2024271007"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "the cordele dispatch and daily sentinel (cordele, georgia) 1920-1926 [online resource]"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 79.01716, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["cordele (ga.)", "journaux", "newspapers", "crisp", "crisp county (ga.)", "cordele", "georgia", "crisp county", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:13:21.366Z", "title": "The Cordele dispatch and daily sentinel", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2024271007/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2024271008/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1926", "dates": ["[1926 TO 1971]"], "description": ["Daily (except Saturday), April 8, 1926-February 16, 1941 Began with volume no. 9, number 123 (April 8, 1926); ceased with v. 54, no. 58 (Jan. 8, 1971). Stated frequency is daily (except Sunday) but actual frequency continues as daily (except Saturday), January 3, 1941-February 16, 1941. Stated frequency and actual frequency may differ at other times as well. Semiweekly edition carrying its own internal enumeration may have been included as part of this title through February 16, 1941. Merged with: Wilcox County chronicle to form: Cordele dispatch and the Wilcox County chronicle. Volume No. 9, Number 123 (April 8, 1926); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed January 10, 2024). Volume No. 11, Number 25 (December 14, 1927) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed January 10, 2024). Wilcox County chronicle Cordele dispatch and the Wilcox County chronicle"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:38:08.561Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2024271008/", "image_url": [], "index": 8, "language": ["english"], "location": ["crisp", "crisp county", "georgia", "cordele", "united states"], "number": ["2026-04-13t21:30:13", "online resource", "1371042241", "2024271008", "2995-9616"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["the cordele dispatch (cordele, georgia) 1926-1971 [online resource]", "serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 79.01716, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["cordele (ga.)", "journaux", "newspapers", "crisp", "crisp county (ga.)", "cordele", "georgia", "crisp county", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:13:21.366Z", "title": "The Cordele dispatch", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2024271008/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.